Unity Care Clinic – Backend (PHP 8.5 Procedural & MySQLi)
Project Overview

Unity Care Clinic’s backend aims to provide a solid foundation for managing key clinical entities such as patients, departments, and doctors. This first version is built using PHP 8.5 (procedural) and MySQLi, focusing on simplicity, maintainability, and clarity for an initial release.

A central component of this backend is the administration dashboard, which offers administrators a global overview of the clinic’s system through key statistics, charts, and activity summaries. This facilitates better decision-making and efficient supervision of operations.

Core Features
1. Entity Management

Full CRUD operations for major clinic entities:

Patients

Doctors

Departments

Additional requirements:

Entity relationship management (e.g., assign doctors to departments)

Clean interfaces for creating, listing, editing, and deleting records

2. Dashboard & Statistics

A dynamic dashboard will display pertinent system information, including:

Total doctor count, specialties, department performance, etc.

Interactive charts using Chart.js

Optional dynamic refresh for live updates

3. Internationalization (i18n)

Multilingual support via dedicated language files:

fr.php, en.php, es.php, etc.

Users can switch language directly from the dashboard

4. Documentation

All scripts must be properly documented:

Internal comments explaining logic

A complete README (installation, project structure, prerequisites)

Clear and organized folder structure

5. Optional Enhancements (Bonus)

AJAX integration for smooth, asynchronous operations

Modal-based forms for improved UX

Advanced charting and interactive analytics

User Stories
ID	Description
US01 – Patient Management	Admin can create, edit, delete, and list patients
US02 – Department Management	Admin can manage departments
US03 – Doctor Management	Admin can manage doctors and assign them to departments
US04 – Dynamic Statistics	Admin can view dashboard metrics and charts
US05 – Internationalization	User can change the interface language
US06 – Smooth Navigation	AJAX enables faster, asynchronous interactions
