Performance Criteria
Response Time

Ensure fast and acceptable system-wide response times

Memory Usage

Optimize memory consumption for server efficiency

SQL Optimization

Reduce query execution time

Avoid slow operations and bottlenecks

Security Guidelines (PHP Procedural + MySQLi)
SQL Injection Prevention

Use prepared statements

Avoid inline SQL with user input

Data Validation & Sanitization

Validate all incoming data

Escape/sanitize outputs to avoid XSS attacks

XSS Protection

Use filtering functions when displaying user-generated content

Best Practices for PHP Procedural Architecture

DRY Principle: avoid repeating logic; use shared functions

Modularity: separate concerns into reusable modules/files

Naming Conventions: consistent and descriptive naming

Comments: clear documentation for future developers

Error Handling: meaningful error reporting and logging

Database Connection Standards

Store credentials securely (never hard-coded in public files)

Properly open/close database connections

Use prepared statements for all dynamic queries

Implement robust connection-error handling

Avoid unnecessary persistent connections

Technologies Used

PHP 8.5 (Procedural)

MySQLi

Chart.js

HTML/CSS/JavaScript (optional: AJAX, modals)